Title: Mapping a wildcard domain name to an Azure App Services
Description: This post is about how we can map wild card domain to Azure App Service. Why we need to map wild card domains? When we are building SAAS applications it is a good practice to provision the tenants with your application sub domain. For example in case JIRA, when you create an instance your instance will be https://instance-name.atlassian.net/. And you need wild card SSL as well for running the instance of HTTPS.
